begin_memory_text: We talked about what we do for work and found out that we both work for our respective local governments, and some of the similarities between her job and one of my previous jobs.
middle_memory_text: We talked about where I was from and about where I had lived - one of the places was a known cold weather state. Then we talked about places she had traveled and some of the coldest weather she had experienced.
end_memory_text: The last thing we talked about was the COVID-19 virus and how it's affected people around us. She mentioned having a coworker pass away pretty suddenly from it and we talked about how it's hard to know whether or not you're high risk and what things you should be doing to protect yourself.
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week will go much the same as it's been going for the last few months. I will have my usual work routine at home and then my usual post-work routine of either playing on my Switch or watching TV with my husband. Maybe we'll go look at some stars too. Altogether unexciting.
critical_positive: I think my conversation partner and I had good chemistry. We had some good similarities with each other which led to easy conversation topics. There was a good flow for the most part, only a few silences while one of us was coming up with something else to move on to.
critical_negative: I think the only real issue I noticed is that since we were strangers it was hard to gauge when the other was done speaking. There were a couple of times when I was wanting to say something and she would keep going with a thought that I had thought was finished and I'm sure it happened on her end as well.

begin_memory_text: We talked about what we did for work and the local government. We talked about courts and municipal in particular. We also talked a bit about our animals.
middle_memory_text: We talked about what we like to do. She told me about singing in a choir. We also talked about where we were from and where we grew up. We talked about cold places to live.
end_memory_text: We talked about places to travel and how covid has ruined plans. She told me how covid had canceled her and her husbands honeymoon. They had been married a year and put off their honeymoon till now. She told me where they went instead. She told me about their drive to Colorado and transporting the telescope there.
rest_of_day_open: I am half way through the week so I hope the rest of the week is not too busy or stressful. Thursday i go into the office so it is always a little more busy than when I work from home. Friday and Saturday are my busy days for my second job so I hope they run smooth.
critical_positive: I think the conversation flowed. We had jobs in common which gave us something to talk about that the start. We were also able to talk about a hobby of mine and how it related to her. She told me how her travel plans to Austria and Switzerland were ruined by covid.
critical_negative: I think it may have run a bit smoother if we had some more things in common. Although I think we did good at finding common ground. I think we had one or two slow moments between changing topics and asking each other new questions. However i think that might be somewhat normal.
